{"id":613,"date":"2022-01-02T17:41:17","date_gmt":"2022-01-02T17:41:17","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=613"},"modified":"2022-01-04T10:27:01","modified_gmt":"2022-01-04T10:27:01","slug":"installation-of-a-centos","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=613","title":{"rendered":"Installation of a CentOS"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left\"><strong>The first step<\/strong> towards getting this certification is obvious. <strong>We need a test environment on which we can train<\/strong>. Although Red Hat OS, shortly RHEL is a proprietary software, we can bypass this by installing <strong>CentOS<\/strong>, which is almost the <strong>absolute free copy of Red Hat<\/strong> without the paid support which is used by large enterprises. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can see all the differences <a href=\"https:\/\/www.openlogic.com\/blog\/centos-vs-redhat\">here<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>There are again many ways to install Linux OS, but I think the 3 main are:<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Your own hardware (you can singleboot or dualboot)<\/li><li>Using a cloud service provider<\/li><li>Using a virtualization tool<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>I wouldn&#8217;t recommend using your own hardware because the main reason we are installing this OS is to <strong>LEARN. And learning means failing, which in this context means breaking your own system, possible damaging your hardware and losing your data.<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You could use a cloud provider and get pretty cheap or even free virtual machine hosting, but I think this choice is less practical if your own hardware can run KVM aka run a virtual machine.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Running a virtual machine on your PC<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>There are many software solutions for this and even more guides how to do so. For practical reasons, I won&#8217;t go that heavy on the details. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>To run a VM I prefer to use a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.virtualbox.org\/\">VirtualBox<\/a> which is more than enough for my needs. I think one other honorable mention should be a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.vmware.com\/topics\/glossary\/content\/virtual-machine.html\">VMware<\/a> which is equally popular, and you can see the main differences <a href=\"https:\/\/www.geeksforgeeks.org\/difference-between-vmware-and-virtualbox\/\">here<\/a>. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>So the process of installing should look like this<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li><strong>Download VirtualBox<\/strong> from their official site and run the installation process.<\/li><li><strong>Download the ISO of a CentOS<\/strong>. You can find the most recent one on their site, but I&#8217;m studying for a RHSA 8 which is running a RHEL 8 version, so logically we need CentOS 8 as well. You can download it<a href=\"https:\/\/www.centos.org\/download\/\"> here<\/a>.<\/li><li><strong>Click new in the VirtualBox application<\/strong>, pick a name and the type and version which is Linux \/ Red Hat 64 bits<\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"435\" height=\"340\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-2.png?resize=435%2C340&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-614\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-2.png?w=435&amp;ssl=1 435w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-2.png?resize=300%2C234&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-2.png?resize=24%2C19&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-2.png?resize=36%2C28&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-2.png?resize=48%2C38&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 435px) 100vw, 435px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>4. <strong>Then choose an<\/strong> <strong>amount of RAM you want to use<\/strong>. You should use at least 2Gb, but I prefer more, so I decided for a 4\u00a0GB.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-3.png?resize=413%2C110&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-615\" width=\"413\" height=\"110\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-3.png?w=413&amp;ssl=1 413w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-3.png?resize=300%2C80&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-3.png?resize=24%2C6&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-3.png?resize=36%2C10&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-3.png?resize=48%2C13&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 413px) 100vw, 413px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>5.  After that the virtual box asks you a few preferences which I&#8217;ll just speed run.<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"alignleft size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"427\" height=\"134\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-4.png?resize=427%2C134&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-616\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-4.png?w=427&amp;ssl=1 427w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-4.png?resize=300%2C94&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-4.png?resize=24%2C8&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-4.png?resize=36%2C11&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-4.png?resize=48%2C15&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 427px) 100vw, 427px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-5.png?resize=404%2C167&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-617\" width=\"404\" height=\"167\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-5.png?w=404&amp;ssl=1 404w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-5.png?resize=300%2C124&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-5.png?resize=24%2C10&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-5.png?resize=36%2C15&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-5.png?resize=48%2C20&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 404px) 100vw, 404px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"alignleft size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"410\" height=\"253\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-6.png?resize=410%2C253&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-618\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-6.png?w=410&amp;ssl=1 410w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-6.png?resize=300%2C185&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-6.png?resize=24%2C15&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-6.png?resize=36%2C22&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-6.png?resize=48%2C30&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 410px) 100vw, 410px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"alignright size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"418\" height=\"205\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-7.png?resize=418%2C205&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-619\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-7.png?w=418&amp;ssl=1 418w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-7.png?resize=300%2C147&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-7.png?resize=24%2C12&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-7.png?resize=36%2C18&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-7.png?resize=48%2C24&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 418px) 100vw, 418px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>6. When you are finished, we still need to dial out few settings<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>I recommend setting up a CPU to use more than 1 core. I usually use 4. <\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"496\" height=\"200\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-9.png?resize=496%2C200&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-621\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-9.png?w=496&amp;ssl=1 496w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-9.png?resize=300%2C121&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-9.png?resize=24%2C10&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-9.png?resize=36%2C15&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-9.png?resize=48%2C19&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 496px) 100vw, 496px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>And <strong>setting up your video memory to maximum settings<\/strong>, so the VM feels less laggy in graphical desktop, which we will use. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"507\" height=\"122\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-10.png?resize=507%2C122&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-622\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-10.png?w=507&amp;ssl=1 507w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-10.png?resize=300%2C72&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-10.png?resize=24%2C6&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-10.png?resize=36%2C9&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-10.png?resize=48%2C12&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 507px) 100vw, 507px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>The last setting should be adding the downloaded CentOS ISO into the virtual SATA input, so the VM thinks it&#8217;s the CD.<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"510\" height=\"156\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-11.png?resize=510%2C156&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-623\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-11.png?w=510&amp;ssl=1 510w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-11.png?resize=300%2C92&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-11.png?resize=24%2C7&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-11.png?resize=36%2C11&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-11.png?resize=48%2C15&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 510px) 100vw, 510px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ok now start our VM, and I&#8217;ll guide you through the installation process.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>First pres <strong>Enter <\/strong>to install the Cent OS<\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"553\" height=\"231\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-12.png?resize=553%2C231&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-624\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-12.png?w=553&amp;ssl=1 553w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-12.png?resize=300%2C125&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-12.png?resize=24%2C10&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-12.png?resize=36%2C15&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-12.png?resize=48%2C20&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 553px) 100vw, 553px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>2. <strong>Now choose your preferred language and keyboard layout<\/strong>. I&#8217;ll be using an US English for both.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>3. You should see a screen like this. Note that there is a bug in which the screen is slightly cut, I&#8217;ve seen this many times, it&#8217;s probably due to a hardware error, and we can just ignore that.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"489\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-16.png?resize=640%2C489&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-628\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-16.png?w=790&amp;ssl=1 790w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-16.png?resize=300%2C229&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-16.png?resize=768%2C587&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-16.png?resize=24%2C18&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-16.png?resize=36%2C28&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-16.png?resize=48%2C37&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>4. We can see a few things are marked with red triangle, we need to fix those. <strong>First click on the Installation Destination.<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"495\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-17.png?resize=640%2C495&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-629\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-17.png?w=797&amp;ssl=1 797w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-17.png?resize=300%2C232&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-17.png?resize=768%2C595&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-17.png?resize=24%2C19&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-17.png?resize=36%2C28&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-17.png?resize=48%2C37&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>There are few ways how to install this OS now. The first, easier, is to just press Done and the system will automatically do the partitioning for us. But this is a guide for Linux administration, so we want problems, always! <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Installation CentOS using a custom partitioning <\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>When you are in the installation destination menu, <strong>press Custom Storage Configuration<\/strong> and just click done in upper right corner. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"531\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-18.png?resize=640%2C531&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-630\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-18.png?w=795&amp;ssl=1 795w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-18.png?resize=300%2C249&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-18.png?resize=768%2C638&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-18.png?resize=24%2C20&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-18.png?resize=36%2C30&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-18.png?resize=48%2C40&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>We are in the Custom partitioning menu<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now click on the + icon, and we will start making a mount points.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"467\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-19.png?resize=640%2C467&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-631\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-19.png?w=798&amp;ssl=1 798w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-19.png?resize=300%2C219&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-19.png?resize=768%2C560&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-19.png?resize=24%2C18&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-19.png?resize=36%2C26&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-19.png?resize=48%2C35&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>The first partition should be the root<\/strong>. We can find it as a slash icon in the mount points menu. And specify the desired capacity. As you can see, I&#8217;ve 32 GIB dedicated to this VM, so I just use 20GIB for root.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>Note: 1 GB is 1000 Mbs but 1 GIB is = 1024 Mbs<\/p><\/blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>You should see the new partition in the partition menu. <\/strong>As the last step of the adding new partition to the system, we need to change the type from LVM to Standard type because it&#8217;s not possible to boot from LVM partition.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>We will now repeat the process for the last remaining partition, which is &#8220;swap&#8221; with 2 GIB of space<\/strong>. This should automatically set the Device type for SWAP, but if not, then you do so.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"493\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-23.png?resize=640%2C493&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-635\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-23.png?w=797&amp;ssl=1 797w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-23.png?resize=300%2C231&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-23.png?resize=768%2C592&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-23.png?resize=24%2C18&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-23.png?resize=36%2C28&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-23.png?resize=48%2C37&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>I&#8217;ve left some space, so we can play with it later, so you should do the same, but it&#8217;s not unnecessary for the system itself. Now let&#8217;s just pres Done to finish partitioning. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The system will bring up all the changes it&#8217;s going to do which we&#8217;ve just configured.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"333\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-24.png?resize=640%2C333&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-636\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-24.png?w=749&amp;ssl=1 749w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-24.png?resize=300%2C156&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-24.png?resize=24%2C12&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-24.png?resize=36%2C19&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-24.png?resize=48%2C25&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Simply press Accept Changes and continue. <\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You will be back in the installation menu, in which <strong>we need to set up a root password and the new non-root user to use as a login.<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>Note that you should never use a root for as a login in your system for security reasons. <\/p><\/blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>First set a new root password<\/strong>. Mine will be &#8220;password&#8221;. If you are planning on using the system or this is not the virtual machine installation, please use a stronger password.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"195\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-25.png?resize=640%2C195&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-637\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-25.png?w=797&amp;ssl=1 797w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-25.png?resize=300%2C91&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-25.png?resize=768%2C234&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-25.png?resize=24%2C7&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-25.png?resize=36%2C11&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-25.png?resize=48%2C15&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Then press Done and in the menu choose &#8220;create a user&#8221;<\/strong>. Just type your username and password. Mine will be again just the &#8220;password&#8221;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"474\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-26.png?resize=640%2C474&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-638\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-26.png?w=796&amp;ssl=1 796w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-26.png?resize=300%2C222&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-26.png?resize=768%2C569&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-26.png?resize=24%2C18&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-26.png?resize=36%2C27&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-26.png?resize=48%2C36&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>After this, again press Done and confirm all the settings with the &#8220;Begin installation&#8221;.<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In a few minutes the installation is done and all you have to do is to press &#8220;Reboot System&#8221; and your system should be up and running, well when it boots up. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Or you though so! Unfortunately, no, it still proms you to confirm CentOS Linux EULA.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"488\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-28.png?resize=640%2C488&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-640\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-28.png?w=800&amp;ssl=1 800w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-28.png?resize=300%2C229&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-28.png?resize=768%2C586&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-28.png?resize=24%2C18&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-28.png?resize=36%2C27&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-28.png?resize=48%2C37&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>After confirming this, it should finally be completed, and now we can start with the real work!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-29.png?resize=640%2C480&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-641\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-29.png?w=785&amp;ssl=1 785w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-29.png?resize=300%2C225&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-29.png?resize=768%2C576&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-29.png?resize=24%2C18&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-29.png?resize=36%2C27&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-29.png?resize=48%2C36&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>The first step towards getting this certification is obvious. We need a test environment on [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":643,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"nf_dc_page":"","om_disable_all_campaigns":false,"_mi_skip_tracking":false},"categories":[219],"tags":[224,226,222,223,227],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/rhsa-installation.png?fit=1280%2C720&ssl=1","_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/613"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Fcomments&post=613"}],"version-history":[{"count":3,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/613\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":658,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/613\/revisions\/658"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/media\/643"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Fmedia&parent=613"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Fcategories&post=613"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/t